<span class="termsBold"> <em>It is normally recommended that a patient obtains a referral to see a specialist from their General Practitioner. This is not necessary if you do not have a GP or if you do not wish your GP to be involved. However, if you wish to claim payment from your health insurer, you will usually need a GP referral. If medication needs to be prescribed, there are also risks if your GP is not informed as they will not have the whole picture and therefore might not prescribe.</em></span>


